main event: A civilian consultant reported seeing a small, white glowing object the size of a ping pong ball over Miami, Florida in 1956.
interesting points: The object was observed for 20 seconds before fading out.
The object did not appear on radar.
The report concluded the object was likely a balloon.
Other unidentified aerial objects were reported in the area, but were not detected on radar.
The report includes some coded text that is not easily decipherable.
